            "commit": {
                "author": {
                    "date": "2026-06-23T22:29:18Z",
                    "email": "vyasr@nvidia.com",
                    "name": "Vyas Ramasubramani"
                },
                "comment_count": 0,
                "committer": {
                    "date": "2026-06-23T22:29:18Z",
                    "email": "vyasr@nvidia.com",
                    "name": "Vyas Ramasubramani"
                },
                "message": "Emit compile-time error for 'not None' parameters with None default\n\nAdd a compile-time check that rejects parameters declared with 'not None'\nthat also have a default value of None, since the default can never be\nused without raising TypeError at runtime.\n\nPreviously, declarations like 'def f(Foo x not None = None)' compiled\nsilently but the default was unreachable — calling the function without\nthe argument always raised TypeError. Now Cython reports:\n\n    Parameter 'x' is declared 'not None' but has a default value of None\n\nThis applies to extension types, builtin types, untyped args, and\n'object'-typed args when explicitly annotated with 'not None'.\n\nCloses #7762",
                "tree": {
                    "sha": "7bedec3225854655c67f9351c8cfc3b4537af06e",
                    "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cython/cython/git/trees/7bedec3225854655c67f9351c8cfc3b4537af06e"
                },
                "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cython/cython/git/commits/a36c28e12bf11d42ffecc6d0bdcb91f9c2c2904b",
                "verification": {
                    "payload": "tree 7bedec3225854655c67f9351c8cfc3b4537af06e\nparent 3139f7c7437c3496a889ac61cde2a1e12d7f11b8\nauthor Vyas Ramasubramani <vyasr@nvidia.com> 1782253758 -0700\ncommitter Vyas Ramasubramani <vyasr@nvidia.com> 1782253758 -0700\n\nEmit compile-time error for 'not None' parameters with None default\n\nAdd a compile-time check that rejects parameters declared with 'not None'\nthat also have a default value of None, since the default can never be\nused without raising TypeError at runtime.\n\nPreviously, declarations like 'def f(Foo x not None = None)' compiled\nsilently but the default was unreachable — calling the function without\nthe argument always raised TypeError. Now Cython reports:\n\n    Parameter 'x' is declared 'not None' but has a default value of None\n\nThis applies to extension types, builtin types, untyped args, and\n'object'-typed args when explicitly annotated with 'not None'.\n\nCloses #7762\n",
                    "reason": "valid",
